<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Luis Suarez has revealed he is excited to be part of the Atletico Madrid squad after speaking for the first time since his ¬£5.5million move from Barcelona.</p>

<p>The Uruguayan striker trained with his new team-mates for the first time on Friday¬† after saying an emotional farewell to the Catalan giants in a press conference the day before.</p>

<p>The 33-year-old striker - who has signed a two-year deal at Atletico - ended his Barcelona career as the club's third-highest goalscorer of all time, netting 198 goals in 283 appearances.¬†</p>

